Usage: loki <options>

[Option] [Parameters] [Explanation]

 -start                Starts loki, uses default config file
                       if not 'conf' is set

 -cli     <host>       Starts a command-line interface, specify host
                       where application is running or connects
                       locally if leaving parameter blank

 -stop    <host>       Stops loki, specify host where application
                       is running or tries to stop local running instance
                       if leaving parameter blank

 -conf    <file>       Sets the config file to load, specify
                       file location

